%% Diagram: Variable-height measurement and correction flow
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant S as Scroll handler
    participant V as Virtualizer
    participant C as Height cache
    participant D as DOM
    participant R as ResizeObserver

    U->>S: scroll event (rAF batched)
    S->>V: scrollTop changed
    V->>C: lookup heights for range
    C-->>V: measured + estimated mix
    V->>D: render visible window<br/>(transform: translateY)
    D->>R: items mounted
    R-->>V: actual heights via callback
    V->>C: write measured heights
    V->>V: recompute total height,<br/>adjust scroll if anchored
    Note over V,D: If estimates were wrong,<br/>visible jump can occur —<br/>buffer + anchoring mitigates.
